1. Calculate the number of unread messages Marie needs to read after 7 days (since she starts by reading 20 messages a day for the first 7 days). The formula for this is:

\[ \text{Number of unread messages remaining} = \text{Number of unread messages} - 20 \times 7 \]

2. Since she gets 6 new messages a day, we can calculate the number of messages she will have after 7 days:

\[ \text{Number of messages after 7 days} = \text{Number of unread messages} - 20 \times 7 + 6 \times 7 \]

3. To find out how many days it will take her to read all her unread messages, we can subtract the number of unread messages she has already from the total number of unread messages needed:

\[ \text{Days} = \frac{\text{Total number of unread messages needed}}{\text{Number of messages after 7 days}} \]

Let's do the math:

1. Number of unread messages to read after 7 days:
\[ \text{Number of unread messages} = 98 - 20 \times 7 = 98 - 140 = -42 \]

Since the number of unread messages cannot be negative, Marie will need to read all her unread messages before she can read them out of her phone. The answer is:

\[ -42 \] days. 

This means it will take Marie 42 days to read all her unread messages on her phone.
Ground Truth Text:
